launch 4 ec2 instances with same security group and key pair
1st one- default server(10,gp3,http rule add anywhere in edit inbound rules)
2nd one- redhat-one(select redhat,10,gp3)
3rd one- ubuntu-server(select ubuntu, 10,gp3)
4th one- redhat-two(1b)

connect instance one(LInux)
yum install httpd -y
cd /var/www/html/
echo "........">index.html
ll
cd
systemctl start httpd
systemctl enable httpd
curl http://localhost

connect 2nd instance(redhat-one)
dnf install httpd -y
cd /var/www/html/
echo ".....">index.html
ll
cd
systemctl start httpd
systemctl enable httpd
curl http://localhost

connect 3rd server(ubuntu)
apt install -y
apt install apache2 -y
cd /var/www/html/
echo ".....">index.html
ll
cd
systemctl start apache2
curl http://localhost

connect 4th server(redhat-two)
cat /etc/os-release
yum install httpd -y
cd /var/www/html/
echo ".....">index.html
ll
cd
systemctl start httpd
systemctl enable httpd
curl http://localhost

paste the ip addresses of all servers with :80 on edge then youll get the info of servers

to add these servers into group
goto EC2--->target groups--->create--->choose a target(instances)---->name(target-group)--->next--->select all machines--->register

EC2----->load balancers
create--->application load balancer--->name(load-balancer)--->ip(ipv4)--->zone(select 1a,b,c,d)--->sec group(existing)--->target group(select the newly created one)--->save

target--->select all--->register pending groups--->register
paste the dns name on edge gets the output...each timw we refresh we get different server info
